nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values:
Here, you can use [https://whatdreamscost.github.io/Spline-Path-Control/](https://whatdreamscost.github.io/Spline-Path-Control/) to create a video file.

Make sure to match fps, resolution and frame load cap the Spline Editor and the Load Video Node

These are recommended settings for 720p:


**Shape Settings**

Color: Use 100% red

Width: 4

Size: 64 I 64
Paste here the coordinates generated from an external tool, such as Blender, After Effects, etc.

Use here the Resolution of the Blender/ After Effect / etc. Project. It then gets resized to this projects resolution.

Make sure not to go beyond 720p, as this node can become computationally heavy.

Choose if you want to use coordinates from:
1 = Spline Editor on the left
2 = External Tool
3 = Spline-Path-Control Tool/ Input Video

Choose either 
1 = Inpainting 
2 = 1st Frame + CN Workflow

Disconnect the Get_skip_frames node if you don‚Äôt want to offset the point animation or if you encounter the following error due to a mismatch between the number of point animation frames and control images:

"ImageBlend
The size of tensor a (263) must match the size of tensor b (223) at non-singleton dimension 0"
